-- Hong Kong Builders Seek Rule-Exemption for Completed Homes, Newspaper Says
-- Stanley James
-- 2010-06-22T22:51:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/hong-kong-builders-seek-rule-exemption-for-completed-homes-newspaper-says.html

          
          
             Hong Kong’s Real Estate Developers’ 
Association asked the government to exempt completed projects 
from new restrictions on property sales, the South China 
Morning Post quoted Thomas Lam Tat-man, a general manager at 
Henderson Land Development, as saying.   
